</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugnosisgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GnosisGnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/16/02 8:18:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /shout</span><hr size=1> I suppose what bothers me about turning off shout is not the utilitarian aspect of it (you might get trained, etc), but the RP aspect of it.<br>
<br>
Someone talks to you in a normal tone of voice and you hear them, but they shout and you're deaf to it?<br>
<br>
I like shout, and for the life of me I can't think of any good reason that they returned shout to zone wide (people on Norrath must have very good lungs). For example, I've got an &quot;avenge&quot; hotkey with a variety of emotes and such, and one of the actions is shouting, &quot;Curse 'em all! I'll avenge yer untimely death, %t!&quot;  In the good old days, it was a nice way to RP extreme emotion. On occasion I've gotten into loud arguments with people, and naturally we shouted at one another.<br>
<br>
Now, though, are all the old RP opportunities nothing but spam? *sigh* I don't want to give up my old ways, but there is no reason that someone WAY on the other side of the zone should be inflicted with my curses at whatever foul creature has just ambushed me and my friends.<br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
Gnosis Bunglefoot<br>
Still desperately holding on to /shout<br>
